{"id": "ChIJQaU0eACBhYARJDg7uXXUsqY", "rating": 4.6, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_INEXPENSIVE", "userRatingCount": 182, "displayName": {"text": "Outta Sight Pizza II", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJQaU0eACBhYARJDg7uXXUsqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2twRFpVaEthbGw1TmpOSGRYaE9Wa2ROZWtaeVVtYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 3, "text": {"text": "Too salty for my liking but the dough is great - crunchy, chewy, etc. I got the Peking duck slice which was good but also too sweet for a pizza. The other two slices were Gal Pal and Bang Bang and I can see why people like this spot but I think it’s hit or miss depending on the unique toppings and flavors. Also the service wasn’t great, I asked the lady what she would recommend and she told me there are labels next to the pizzas at the window 😅 Overall, not my favorite and would much rather go to Tony’s or Flour + Water.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Too salty for my liking but the dough is great - crunchy, chewy, etc. I got the Peking duck slice which was good but also too sweet for a pizza. The other two slices were Gal Pal and Bang Bang and I can see why people like this spot but I think it’s hit or miss depending on the unique toppings and flavors. Also the service wasn’t great, I asked the lady what she would recommend and she told me there are labels next to the pizzas at the window 😅 Overall, not my favorite and would much rather go to Tony’s or Flour + Water.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jae Jun", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/111176457226777467716/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIjPPHw4K_-pI3GQsWEHgn1Nb4rLAb4ZNGE-MHFS3fPZZK56Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba5"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-11T03:24:14.202964369Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2twRFpVaEthbGw1TmpOSGRYaE9Wa2ROZWtaeVVtYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2twRFpVaEthbGw1TmpOSGRYaE9Wa2ROZWtaeVVtYxAB!2m1!1s0x808581007834a541:0xa6b2d475b93b3824"}, {"name": "places/ChIJQaU0eACBhYARJDg7uXXUsqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2t4MlJETllTRFpCZEc5bU1FVk5la1V3YW5KM1owRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "9 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "I had the down the hatch and the peking duck, and both were amazing. I wouldn't say the thin crust was particularly thin. It was crispy and chewy, which I liked. The peking duck flavor and texture was pretty good, and it somehow worked on pizza with cheese. The thicker crust was also interesting, but I think I prefer the regular crust. Will definitely be back sometime!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I had the down the hatch and the peking duck, and both were amazing. I wouldn't say the thin crust was particularly thin. It was crispy and chewy, which I liked. The peking duck flavor and texture was pretty good, and it somehow worked on pizza with cheese. The thicker crust was also interesting, but I think I prefer the regular crust. Will definitely be back sometime!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Dylan Li", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115227455027475284936/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPaGS9t9-aJJ6PTvp58-WqJZKqXc0pRbA9yuf75hHD0htJMO9o=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2025-09-26T05:07:23.101827774Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2t4MlJETllTRFpCZEc5bU1FVk5la1V3YW5KM1owRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2t4MlJETllTRFpCZEc5bU1FVk5la1V3YW5KM1owRRAB!2m1!1s0x808581007834a541:0xa6b2d475b93b3824"}, {"name": "places/ChIJQaU0eACBhYARJDg7uXXUsqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21RNGNXNVFSMlp1WTJwcFRIZEtOMmxKUlVsMk0xRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "10 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Ever had lettuce on your Pizza?\nI never did until I visited Outta Sight Pizza in SF - and I loved it!\n\nWas in the city for a meeting and found Outta Sight - walked through Chinatown to their shop on Clay Street.  They had Pepperoni and several other traditional pizza flavors but I was intrigued with several new flavors they had on display.  They had a Peking Duck pizza and a \"BLT Slice\" - it was different and unique and that's what I ordered. The Peking Duck pizza is a nod to the cuisine of Chinatown, just up the street.\n\nAfter a few minutes, they had warmed my slice in the pizza over, added shredduce (shredded lettuce) and a topping of finely shredded cheese.  It was a generous size slide (rectangular) for a decent price.  Apart from the crust and mozzarella cheese it had early girl tomatoes, thick bacon, and a garlic aioli.  It was delicious - the flavors worked very well together.  The \"shredduce\" reminded me of a tack with shredded lettuce.\n\nThey have a small indoor seating (like counter seating against the wall) but I opted to walk a block and eat outside on a nice (rare, warm) SF afternoon in Portsmouth Square Park.\n\nShould I find myself in SF again seeking an afternoon meal, I would definitely consider dropping by Outta Sight Pizza and grabbing a slice or two.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Ever had lettuce on your Pizza?\nI never did until I visited Outta Sight Pizza in SF - and I loved it!\n\nWas in the city for a meeting and found Outta Sight - walked through Chinatown to their shop on Clay Street.  They had Pepperoni and several other traditional pizza flavors but I was intrigued with several new flavors they had on display.  They had a Peking Duck pizza and a \"BLT Slice\" - it was different and unique and that's what I ordered. The Peking Duck pizza is a nod to the cuisine of Chinatown, just up the street.\n\nAfter a few minutes, they had warmed my slice in the pizza over, added shredduce (shredded lettuce) and a topping of finely shredded cheese.  It was a generous size slide (rectangular) for a decent price.  Apart from the crust and mozzarella cheese it had early girl tomatoes, thick bacon, and a garlic aioli.  It was delicious - the flavors worked very well together.  The \"shredduce\" reminded me of a tack with shredded lettuce.\n\nThey have a small indoor seating (like counter seating against the wall) but I opted to walk a block and eat outside on a nice (rare, warm) SF afternoon in Portsmouth Square Park.\n\nShould I find myself in SF again seeking an afternoon meal, I would definitely consider dropping by Outta Sight Pizza and grabbing a slice or two.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Chet Davis", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/118025817438566990382/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRZJJF_nSOLM6zwzmWdT9J7udpY10qy6wLGf8GRyndzjtf0FeD=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2025-09-03T17:24:27.963450376Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21RNGNXNVFSMlp1WTJwcFRIZEtOMmxKUlVsMk0xRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21RNGNXNVFSMlp1WTJwcFRIZEtOMmxKUlVsMk0xRRAB!2m1!1s0x808581007834a541:0xa6b2d475b93b3824"}, {"name": "places/ChIJQaU0eACBhYARJDg7uXXUsqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkZlUwMUNVMUF0YTB0RlNVVXRia3AwY2xCcmRsRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Very flavorful pizza 🍕 and the portions were more than enough.  I like the Peking Duck pizza.  FYI-There is no bathroom here for customers to use.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Very flavorful pizza 🍕 and the portions were more than enough.  I like the Peking Duck pizza.  FYI-There is no bathroom here for customers to use.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Matilda Rios", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/109033790923686696594/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWdwkPFerC4Mk8d5TBdwrapv1VC_RQGe3znmKGEpsQm4ObIHE2s=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba6"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-25T01:51:18.132334355Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkZlUwMUNVMUF0YTB0RlNVVXRia3AwY2xCcmRsRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkZlUwMUNVMUF0YTB0RlNVVXRia3AwY2xCcmRsRRAB!2m1!1s0x808581007834a541:0xa6b2d475b93b3824"}, {"name": "places/ChIJQaU0eACBhYARJDg7uXXUsqY/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pCWWVWZEtWVEl4VWxWRlEwVnljRGRCYWtGTFNsRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Former Tony's convert, now this place is my post-gym snack! Thanks to Z and all of the other lovely faces at the front. The pizza is bangin', but I come back to places that remember me and don't just say \"what can I get you\" as soon as you get to the counter. Service and taste are unparalleled. 👍🏻 ✨\n\nImagine a slice of pepperoni pizza, hot and meaty with freshly crisped basil, steaming right out of the oven covered with freshly grated parm. Well, you don't have to I included a picture. But get that.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Former Tony's convert, now this place is my post-gym snack! Thanks to Z and all of the other lovely faces at the front. The pizza is bangin', but I come back to places that remember me and don't just say \"what can I get you\" as soon as you get to the counter. Service and taste are unparalleled. 👍🏻 ✨\n\nImagine a slice of pepperoni pizza, hot and meaty with freshly crisped basil, steaming right out of the oven covered with freshly grated parm. Well, you don't have to I included a picture. But get that.", "languageCode": "en"}, "au